```python
def is_prime(num):
    if num < 2:
        return False
    for i in range(2, int(num**0.5) + 1):
        if num % i == 0:
            return False
    return True

# Test it
print(is_prime(29)) # True
print(is_prime(15)) # False
```
Checks divisibility up to the square root. Efficient enough for most day-to-day prime checks.

